
*** Testing REST ***

cURL is a nice tool to test RESTful services

Testing the resources from command line. 
NOTE: See Json further below
--------------------------------------------

# GET (find). 
curl -v -H "Accept: application/json" http://localhost:8080/rest_backend/webresources/response 
curl -v -H "Accept: application/json" http://localhost:8080/rest_backend/webresources/response/11
curl -v -H "Accept: application/json" http://localhost:8080/rest_backend/webresources/response/count

# NOTE Quotes!
curl -v -H "Accept: application/json" "http://localhost:8080/rest_backend/webresources/response/range?fst=2&count=10"

# POST (create)
curl -v  http://localhost:8080/rest_backend/webresources/response --request POST --data "id=999&fname=***CREATE***&age=999"

# PUT (update)
# Must have pnumb in request
curl -v http://localhost:8080/rest_backend/webresources/response/11 --request PUT --data "fname=***UPDATE***"

# DELETE (delete)
curl -v http://localhost:8080/rest_backend/webresources/response/11 --request DELETE




